text: The 2016 Pacific hurricane season was an event in the annual cycle of tropical cyclone formation. It officially began May 15, 2016 in the eastern Pacific, designated as the area east of 140°W, and began on June 1, 2016 in the central Pacific, which is between the International Date Line and 140°W. Both seasons officially ended on November 30, 2016. These dates conventionally delimit the period of each year when most tropical cyclones form in the eastern Pacific basin. ==Storms== ===Hurricane Pali=== ===Tropical Depression One-E=== ===Tropical Storm Agatha=== ===Major Hurricane Blas=== ===Hurricane Celia=== ===Major Hurricane Darby=== ===Tropical Storm Estelle=== ===Hurricane Frank=== ===Major Hurricane Georgette=== ===Tropical Storm Howard === ===Tropical Storm Ivette=== ===Tropical Storm Javier=== ===Tropical Storm Kay=== ===Major Hurricane Lester=== ===Major Hurricane Madeline=== ===Hurricane Newton=== ===Hurricane Orlene=== ===Hurricane Paine=== ===Tropical Storm Roslyn=== ===Hurricane Ulika=== ===Major Hurricane Seymour=== ===Tropical Storm Tina=== ===Tropical Storm Otto=== On November 25, Major Hurricane Otto entered the basin. ==Related pages== *2006 Atlantic hurricane season ==Other websites== * National Hurricane Center's Eastern Pacific Tropical Weather Outlook - updated four times daily * National Hurricane Center * National Hurricane Center's 2016 Advisory Archive * Central Pacific Hurricane Center Pacific hurricane season Category:Pacific hurricane seasons
